# ERP code quality & structure

Follow `.cursor/rules/erp-project-structure.mdc` layers **without exception**. This rule adds the quality bar.

## Structure non-negotiables

- **One API route per module** (`/api/sales`, `/api/procurement`, `/api/inventory`) — extend with `resource` param, never add parallel routes for the same domain  
- **Business logic in `src/lib/server/`** — never in `page.tsx` or route handlers beyond auth + dispatch  
- **Shared UI** in `src/components/modules/*-shared.tsx` (columns, headers) — not copy-pasted per page  
- **Cross-module concerns** in dedicated libs (`src/lib/documents/`, `src/lib/sales/below-cost.ts`, etc.)  
- **Types** in `src/lib/types/index.ts` until split is justified (>300 lines in types file)  

## Before finishing a task

1. `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` — fix type errors  
2. Match naming/style of the nearest completed module (Sales → Procurement → Inventory)  
3. Wire UI end-to-end: list → dialog → `lib/data` → API → server → migration (if needed)  
4. Run docs sync per `erp-docs-and-features.mdc`  

## Optional / admin features

- Add `feat_*` in `feature-flags.ts` + admin toggle on Feature Management page  
- Server must respect flag (do not rely on UI-only hiding)  
- Per-company settings → migration + `src/app/api/admin/...` + admin page section  

## File size & clarity

- Split files approaching **500 lines**  
- No duplicate totals/calculations — use `src/lib/sales/calculations.ts`  
- Comments only for non-obvious business rules (VAT, UAE compliance, approval flows)  

